/**
 * @page faq Frequently Asked Questions
 *
 * @tableofcontents
 *
 * @section faq_general General
 *
 * @subsection faq_what_is What is common_game_server?
 *
 * It is a unified C++20 game server framework that combines an Entity-Component
 * System (ECS), a hot-reloadable plugin architecture, and 5 horizontally scalable
 * microservices. It is built on top of the kcenon ecosystem (Tier 3 application
 * layer).
 *
 * @subsection faq_who_for Who is it for?
 *
 * Game studios building multiplayer game servers in C++20 who want a
 * production-ready foundation with cloud-native deployment, observability,
 * and a clear extension model via plugins.
 *
 * @subsection faq_license What license is it under?
 *
 * BSD 3-Clause License. You can use it commercially without royalty obligations.
 * See LICENSE in the project root.
 *
 * @section faq_build Build & Setup
 *
 * @subsection faq_compiler Which compilers are supported?
 *
 * GCC 11+, Clang 14+, Apple Clang 14+, MSVC 2022+. C++20 is required.
 * See COMPATIBILITY.md for the full matrix.
 *
 * @subsection faq_conan_or_vcpkg Conan or vcpkg?
 *
 * Conan 2 is the primary package manager. vcpkg is supported via the
 * `conan-release` and `vcpkg` CMake presets. Pick whichever fits your
 * existing toolchain.
 *
 * @subsection faq_hot_reload How do I enable plugin hot reload?
 *
 * Configure with `-DCGS_HOT_RELOAD=ON`. **This is development-only** —
 * production builds must leave it OFF for security and stability. See
 * ADR-003 for the rationale.
 *
 * @section faq_ecs Entity-Component System
 *
 * @subsection faq_why_ecs Why ECS instead of OOP hierarchies?
 *
 * Performance, composition flexibility, and parallelism. ECS gives us
 * cache-friendly data layout, O(1) component add/remove, and DAG-based
 * parallel system execution. See ADR-002 for the full reasoning.
 *
 * @subsection faq_max_entities What is the maximum entity count?
 *
 * The framework targets 10,000 entities processed in < 5 ms per tick (20 Hz).
 * Higher counts work but require profiling. The hard limit is the entity
 * version recycling space (currently 64 bits, effectively unlimited).
 *
 * @section faq_plugins Plugins
 *
 * @subsection faq_plugin_lang Can I write plugins in languages other than C++?
 *
 * Currently, plugins must export a C++ ABI (`cgs_create_plugin()` returning
 * a `cgs::plugin::GamePlugin*`). Bindings to scripting languages (Lua,
 * Python) are out of scope for v0.x and may be considered post-1.0.
 *
 * @subsection faq_plugin_state How does plugin state survive a hot reload?
 *
 * Plugins implement `serialize`/`deserialize` hooks that snapshot their
 * state to a flat byte buffer before unload, then restore it after the
 * new version is loaded. State is held in framework-managed memory during
 * the swap.
 *
 * @section faq_services Microservices
 *
 * @subsection faq_why_5 Why exactly 5 services?
 *
 * Each service represents a distinct scaling profile and failure domain
 * (Auth, Gateway, Game, Lobby, DBProxy). Splitting further would add
 * inter-service overhead without benefit; merging would prevent
 * independent scaling. See ADR-004.
 *
 * @subsection faq_inter_service How do services communicate?
 *
 * gRPC over TLS for production; UNIX domain sockets in local development.
 * Correlation IDs flow through every hop for distributed tracing.
 *
 * @section faq_kcenon kcenon Ecosystem
 *
 * @subsection faq_why_kcenon Why depend on kcenon ecosystem instead of bundled libraries?
 *
 * Each kcenon foundation system is independently versioned, benchmarked,
 * and stress-tested. Ecosystem improvements (logging, network, etc.) are
 * inherited automatically without re-implementing them in this project.
 * See ECOSYSTEM.md.
 *
 * @subsection faq_pin_versions Should I pin the kcenon dependency versions?
 *
 * Yes. The project pins to release tags via `cmake/kcenon_deps.cmake`.
 * See DEPENDENCY_MATRIX.md for the current required versions.
 *
 * @section faq_more More Help
 *
 * - troubleshooting.dox — Common build/runtime issues
 * - guides/FAQ.md — Additional FAQs
 * - GitHub Discussions: https://github.com/kcenon/common_game_server/discussions
 */
